      <h1><span class="position">#401</span> ActionController::Live <em>pro</em></h1>
      <div class="details">Jan 19, 2013 | 14 minutes | <a href="/?tag_id=11">Ajax</a>, <a href="/?tag_id=38">Rails 4.0</a></div>
      <div class="description">Server-sent events allow you to trigger events on the browser from a persistent connection to the server. This requires Rails stream data which can be done through ActionController::Live, a feature upcoming in Rails 4.</div>
      <div class="watch"><a href="/pro" class="pretty_button">Subscribe to Watch Episode</a></div>
